questionRound.0.question.11.answer: Typically assuming that the 6th player would chose the highest row according to the 1st's choice  I would work my way backward logically along the same lines until I came to my position.

I would look first at the payoff of the last colour and see which of my choices would result in their greatest benefit. Then I would work backwards  assuming each person would choose their personal greatest benefit without screwing anyone else over and would chose x or y depending on which choice would make that pattern optimal (i.e. most tokens for most people)

I would look at the first color and determine what the last color would choice. Work backwards until my color. Sometimes I take a little risk hoping someone would just simply choose the largest number so I get a bigger number when they end up getting a small number.
seeing 2 blocks ahead to predict what others might do

basically you have to find out if it has a dominate strategy. if not then find out who determines/affects you choices. then predict what it will pick. etc etc and then determine the whole process backwards.
I looked for which option was the highest reward for the color after me to see what they might pick. I determined what I thought to be their most beneficial choice and chose mine accordingly.

Purple would usually have a completely dominant strategy (where one row is clearly better than the other row). Once you know purple's choice  just work backwards to pick the optimal choice given purple's choice. Given Maroon's optimal choice  orange would pick his/her optimal choice and so on.

Basically you wanted to be "generous" because that way people could maximize the total tokens and the game could go relatively smoothly. You also wanted to backtrace the best possible move  starting from the first square and then moving backwards  selecting the best outcome for the player given their options. That therefore  maximized your score.
If everyone pursues their best interest  you know what to do every time. The only way you can go wrong is if another player makes a choice not in his best interest.
generally i picked the one that would yioeld the highest put come based on what i thought the person after me would chopose

You are able to select what pay out the person before you receives. If everyone chooses whats in the best intrest of the person before them everytime  the maximum amount of money will be gained overall

I was playing by looking ahead two individuals' payoffs. I guessed that the person after me would choose the best payoff option given the choice by the person after him/her. This helped most of the time  but not always  about 20% of the time  it didn't work. I was hoping to get the higher amount in the given row  but the choice of the person after me was not always as I expected. It was the easiest when I was the last or the second to last person to make the choice because the first person in the order has already made his/her choice  and my payoff is contengent upon his/hers.
